Hey, Aaron?

562
00:32:36,796 --> 00:32:37,979
Hello?

563
00:32:40,859 --> 00:32:43,771
This is my nice voice.

564
00:32:50,395 --> 00:32:51,771
Aaron?

565
00:33:00,636 --> 00:33:01,660
Shit.

566
00:33:04,219 --> 00:33:07,228
Aaron? I want to get down now.

567
00:33:09,722 --> 00:33:10,972
Shit.

568
00:33:11,867 --> 00:33:12,988
Hello!

569
00:33:19,164 --> 00:33:21,403
No! No!

570
00:33:30,011 --> 00:33:32,188
Put me down--

571
00:33:37,404 --> 00:33:38,364
This isn't funny--

572
00:33:41,980 --> 00:33:42,940
Aaron!

573
00:33:48,444 --> 00:33:49,564
Aaron!

574
00:33:54,491 --> 00:33:55,484
Aaron!

575
00:33:55,612 --> 00:33:57,691
No!

576
00:33:58,108 --> 00:33:59,228
Help!

577
00:34:00,156 --> 00:34:01,116
Get me out!

578
00:34:01,244 --> 00:34:03,004
This hurts!

579
00:34:03,131 --> 00:34:04,028
Aaron!

580
00:34:04,156 --> 00:34:05,916
Hello!

581
00:34:10,811 --> 00:34:13,372
What the fuck?

582
00:34:15,644 --> 00:34:16,827
No, wait!

583
00:34:18,811 --> 00:34:20,348
Shit!

584
00:34:20,859 --> 00:34:22,172
Oh, my God, please!

585
00:34:22,300 --> 00:34:23,739
No, wait!

586
00:34:23,868 --> 00:34:26,076
Hey, you stay away from me!

587
00:34:27,419 --> 00:34:28,764
Get away!

588
00:34:30,459 --> 00:34:32,668
No, please, wait!

589
00:34:38,171 --> 00:34:41,148
Please! Please!

590
00:34:43,580 --> 00:34:44,762
Please!

591
00:34:47,420 --> 00:34:50,491
Stop, please! Please, please!

592
00:34:50,619 --> 00:34:52,539
I don't want to die!

593
00:34:56,700 --> 00:34:58,171
Tatum!

594
00:35:02,396 --> 00:35:04,252
Motherfucker!

595
00:35:14,844 --> 00:35:16,892
Cover the exits!

596
00:35:19,931 --> 00:35:21,242
Oh, God. Okay.

597
00:35:28,795 --> 00:35:30,044
Tatum!

598
00:35:30,842 --> 00:35:32,220
Mom, what are you doing?
Oh, God!

599
00:35:32,348 --> 00:35:35,196
Are you okay?
Oh, good... okay... okay.

600
00:35:46,299 --> 00:35:47,868
I wasn't even here.
I had already left.

601
00:35:47,995 --> 00:35:49,212
He was home with me.

602
00:35:49,756 --> 00:35:50,971
Okay. Where were you?

603
00:35:52,444 --> 00:35:54,044
I was downstairs
in the costume shop.

604
00:35:54,172 --> 00:35:56,411
Not when I was there.
Wait, you were here?

605
00:35:56,540 --> 00:35:57,787
No, he left and I was there.

606
00:35:57,916 --> 00:36:00,220
But I didn't see you.

607
00:36:00,348 --> 00:36:02,300
I was in the dressing rooms.

608
00:36:02,427 --> 00:36:03,676
The whole time?

609
00:36:04,442 --> 00:36:07,259
No. Not the whole time.

610
00:36:07,387 --> 00:36:09,724
I went home,
had a light dinner,
Aperol Spritz.

611
00:36:09,851 --> 00:36:12,444
My God, who would do
something like this?

612
00:36:12,572 --> 00:36:14,651
We don't even
have an understudy.

613
00:36:14,780 --> 00:36:17,500
Hey.
Hey.

614
00:36:17,628 --> 00:36:19,612
So, the killer fled.

615
00:36:19,739 --> 00:36:21,916
Whoever did this
knew their way around here.

616
00:36:22,044 --> 00:36:24,092
It was well-thought-out
and executed.

617
00:36:24,220 --> 00:36:25,916
What about the kids?
Did you call your mom?

618
00:36:26,044 --> 00:36:27,292
I called.

619
00:36:27,419 --> 00:36:29,916
The entire Denver police force
is with them, they're safe.

620
00:36:31,322 --> 00:36:32,988
Two teens are dead.

621
00:36:33,115 --> 00:36:34,876
Mark, what the fuck?

622
00:36:37,212 --> 00:36:38,588
You are not alone.

623
00:36:39,324 --> 00:36:40,540
We got this.

624
00:36:41,436 --> 00:36:43,900
If this is Stu...
It's not Stu.

625
00:36:44,028 --> 00:36:47,132
It's not.
He is buried in Woodsboro.

626
00:36:47,260 --> 00:36:49,404
Look, we are taking that
phone call that you recorded,

627
00:36:49,531 --> 00:36:50,972
we're sending it
to the state police.

628
00:36:51,100 --> 00:36:53,307
They have the resources
to determine who it is.

629
00:36:53,435 --> 00:36:54,748
We are gonna get him.

630
00:36:56,028 --> 00:36:58,300
Isn't Ben a computer junkie?

631
00:36:59,292 --> 00:37:00,700
Aren't all kids?

632
00:37:00,828 --> 00:37:04,188
He applied to Carnegie Mellon
to study computer science.

633
00:37:04,316 --> 00:37:07,420
I hear you.
But anybody can do
deepfakes these days.

634
00:37:08,762 --> 00:37:10,140
Why don't you get Tatum?

635
00:37:10,268 --> 00:37:12,156
Just give me a minute and then
we'll get out of here.

636
00:37:16,411 --> 00:37:17,916
Tatum, we're going.

637
00:37:19,132 --> 00:37:20,316
Not you.

638
00:37:21,179 --> 00:37:22,716
Mom.
Answer's no.

639
00:37:22,844 --> 00:37:23,804
But, Mrs. Evans--

640
00:37:23,932 --> 00:37:25,116
No.

641
00:37:28,124 --> 00:37:30,172
It's okay.
You go with your family.

642
00:37:31,420 --> 00:37:32,731
I'll call you.

643
00:37:39,964 --> 00:37:41,724
Why do you treat him
like that?

644
00:37:42,524 --> 00:37:43,420
He's not a killer.

645
00:37:43,548 --> 00:37:44,476
You don't know that.

646
00:37:44,604 --> 00:37:47,580
Not everyone is Billy Loomis.

647
00:37:47,708 --> 00:37:49,148
Just because you can't
trust people,

648
00:37:49,276 --> 00:37:51,292
doesn't mean people can't
be trusted.

649
00:37:51,996 --> 00:37:53,276
We're not doing this here.

650
00:38:07,291 --> 00:38:09,851
They'll sweep the house.
Yeah. We'll be quick, Chief.

651
00:38:30,363 --> 00:38:31,516
All clear.

652
00:38:32,283 --> 00:38:33,436
We're gonna
secure the neighborhood.

653
00:38:33,564 --> 00:38:34,811
Great.
We'll only be a few minutes.

654
00:38:34,940 --> 00:38:36,123
Come on.
Thank you.

655
00:38:39,772 --> 00:38:41,819
Grab your stuff.
You leave in five.

656
00:38:42,652 --> 00:38:44,956
Wait. You're not
coming with us?

657
00:38:45,084 --> 00:38:47,291
It's my job to catch
whoever's doing this.

658
00:39:02,716 --> 00:39:03,644
Where's your go bag?

659
00:39:03,772 --> 00:39:05,692
I unpacked it
a long time ago.

660
00:39:05,820 --> 00:39:07,196
Damn it, Tatum.

661
00:39:11,868 --> 00:39:13,308
So, what? We just run?

662
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:16,028
Yes, we do.

663
00:39:16,156 --> 00:39:18,556
I thought the great
Sidney Prescott never ran.

664
00:39:18,684 --> 00:39:20,348
With you it's different.

665
00:39:20,924 --> 00:39:22,203
They killed Hannah, Mom.

666
00:39:22,332 --> 00:39:24,892
We can't just leave.
Listen, I know this story,

667
00:39:25,020 --> 00:39:27,259
and if we stay,
more people will die.

668
00:39:27,388 --> 00:39:30,460
I'm sorry, but I'm not gonna
risk you getting hurt.

669
00:39:32,124 --> 00:39:33,308
Why didn't you warn me?

670
00:39:33,436 --> 00:39:35,068
About what?
All of this!

671
00:39:35,196 --> 00:39:37,819
If-If I was ready,
maybe I could have saved her.

672
00:39:37,948 --> 00:39:39,388
Maybe I could have
done something.

673
00:39:39,516 --> 00:39:40,764
If you need anything else,
pack it.

674
00:39:40,892 --> 00:39:42,844
Mom, why can't you just
trust me?

675
00:39:42,971 --> 00:39:45,308
We need to go! Okay?

676
00:39:50,748 --> 00:39:52,092
Here, take these.

677
00:39:52,219 --> 00:39:53,980
Why did you
turn the light out?

678
00:39:54,588 --> 00:39:55,740
I thought you did.

679
00:39:59,643 --> 00:40:00,603
Tatum.

680
00:40:00,732 --> 00:40:02,044
Stay behind me.

681
00:40:08,156 --> 00:40:09,340
Tatum.

682
00:40:11,419 --> 00:40:12,412
Tatum.

683
00:40:19,132 --> 00:40:20,284
Dad.

684
00:40:23,388 --> 00:40:25,596
Please, leave her alone.

685
00:40:29,051 --> 00:40:30,588
Mark, put the gun down.

686
00:40:37,404 --> 00:40:39,805
Hon, it's gonna be okay.

687
00:40:39,932 --> 00:40:41,052
Just look at me.

688
00:40:44,860 --> 00:40:46,300
It's me that you want.

689
00:40:46,428 --> 00:40:48,828
You just-- you let her go.

690
00:40:53,436 --> 00:40:54,780
Drop!

691
00:41:17,148 --> 00:41:18,076
Mark!
Dad!

692
00:41:24,731 --> 00:41:25,980
Run!

693
00:41:28,956 --> 00:41:30,491
This way!

694
00:41:32,892 --> 00:41:34,939
What-What are you doing?

695
00:41:37,052 --> 00:41:38,428
Fuck off!

696
00:41:41,788 --> 00:41:44,220
Where are we?
We're safe in here.

697
00:41:50,876 --> 00:41:52,733
You sure he can't get inside?
Yeah.

698
00:41:52,860 --> 00:41:54,076
What is that?
It's another way out.

699
00:41:54,204 --> 00:41:55,740
I need to get your dad.
You stay here.

700
00:41:55,868 --> 00:41:57,244
No, you can't leave me, Mom!

701
00:41:59,388 --> 00:42:00,796
Let me go with you, please!

702
00:42:00,924 --> 00:42:02,492
Okay, hurry.

703
00:42:13,404 --> 00:42:14,749
Down to the end. Go.

704
00:42:14,876 --> 00:42:16,060
Okay.

705
00:42:24,251 --> 00:42:25,660
Shh.

706
00:42:47,228 --> 00:42:48,956
Mom!
This way!

707
00:42:51,388 --> 00:42:52,828
Mom!
Go, go, go!

708
00:43:03,259 --> 00:43:04,252
Okay.

709
00:43:12,285 --> 00:43:13,500
Shh--

710
00:43:20,283 --> 00:43:21,340
Go, go, go!

711
00:43:29,468 --> 00:43:30,940
Mom!

712
00:43:31,803 --> 00:43:32,956
Go!

713
00:43:51,805 --> 00:43:53,788
Okay. This way.

714
00:44:14,908 --> 00:44:16,124
Get the police! Go!
Mom!

715
00:44:16,252 --> 00:44:18,876
Help! Somebody help us!

716
00:44:41,852 --> 00:44:43,676
Hey, are you okay?

717
00:44:43,803 --> 00:44:45,788
Are you okay?
Yeah.

718
00:44:45,916 --> 00:44:47,740
God, I love you.
I love you.

719
00:44:52,956 --> 00:44:54,077
Did I get him?

720
00:44:54,460 --> 00:44:55,356
You got him!

721
00:44:55,484 --> 00:44:57,053
Chad, get the camera now.

722
00:44:57,180 --> 00:44:58,396
Mindy, set up for a remote.

723
00:44:58,524 --> 00:45:00,092
Ma'am, you need to stay
inside your vehicle.

724
00:45:00,220 --> 00:45:02,076
You need to get out
of my face.

725
00:45:02,492 --> 00:45:04,060
Mom! Dad!

726
00:45:06,621 --> 00:45:08,059
Are you okay?
I'm okay.

727
00:45:08,188 --> 00:45:10,204
Oh, that was horrifying.
That was awesome.

728
00:45:10,332 --> 00:45:12,285
Grab the camera.
We need B-roll of everything.

729
00:45:12,413 --> 00:45:13,916
You have to be ready
at all times.

730
00:45:14,044 --> 00:45:16,285
In my defense,
I wasn't exactly expecting

731
00:45:16,412 --> 00:45:17,981
to be part
of vehicular manslaughter

732
00:45:18,109 --> 00:45:19,356
the second we roll into town,

733
00:45:19,484 --> 00:45:21,276
but next time...
next time I will be prepared.

734
00:45:24,669 --> 00:45:26,012
Hey.

735
00:45:28,092 --> 00:45:30,461
Chief, you gonna be okay?
Put pressure on it.

736
00:45:30,589 --> 00:45:32,252
Just sit still for a minute.

737
00:45:35,197 --> 00:45:36,572
You're bleeding.

738
00:45:36,700 --> 00:45:38,077
Your point?

739
00:45:44,957 --> 00:45:45,917
How's Mark?

740
00:45:46,045 --> 00:45:48,220
It takes a lot
to bring him down.

741
00:45:51,773 --> 00:45:53,532
Gale, he said he was Stu.

742
00:45:54,557 --> 00:45:55,964
I'm sorry. What did you say?

743
00:45:56,349 --> 00:45:57,309
Stu.

744
00:46:00,252 --> 00:46:01,341
Stu Macher?

745
00:46:01,468 --> 00:46:03,516
Dead Stu Macher?

746
00:46:05,181 --> 00:46:06,524
Let's unmask this fucker.

747
00:46:09,404 --> 00:46:11,036
Chief?
Do it.

748
00:46:15,452 --> 00:46:16,637
Who is that?

749
00:46:16,765 --> 00:46:20,317
I don't know, but I saw him
today in the coffee shop.

750
00:46:20,445 --> 00:46:21,884
Are you sure?
Yeah.

751
00:46:22,012 --> 00:46:24,764
Nobody knows the guy?
Okay, that's weird.

752
00:46:24,892 --> 00:46:27,772
That is weird. It's always
someone you know.

753
00:46:32,861 --> 00:46:35,068
You want more B-roll?
We could make a whole movie.

754
00:46:35,196 --> 00:46:36,444
I don't know what to say.

755
00:46:36,573 --> 00:46:39,388
I meant to brake
and I hit the gas.

756
00:46:45,596 --> 00:46:47,068
Karl Allen Gibbs.

757
00:46:47,197 --> 00:46:49,468
He escaped from Fallbrook
Psychiatric Hospital
two weeks ago.

758
00:46:49,596 --> 00:46:50,876
Triple murderer.

759
00:46:51,005 --> 00:46:54,141
Any idea why he'd come after
you or your family?

760
00:46:54,268 --> 00:46:56,412
No.
Thanks, Cooke.

761
00:46:56,989 --> 00:46:58,236
Chief.

762
00:47:04,509 --> 00:47:05,661
Well...

763
00:47:05,788 --> 00:47:07,228
He's not gonna
hurt anyone else.

764
00:47:07,357 --> 00:47:08,924
No.

765
00:47:09,916 --> 00:47:11,292
This was too easy.

766
00:47:12,700 --> 00:47:13,884
There's always more than one.

767
00:47:14,013 --> 00:47:14,908
Sidney,

768
00:47:15,037 --> 00:47:16,732
Stu Macher is dead.

769
00:47:19,292 --> 00:47:21,116
Watch Tatum for a minute.

770
00:47:23,516 --> 00:47:25,853
Sidney. Sidney!

771
00:47:25,980 --> 00:47:28,381
One question for you, Sidney!

772
00:47:28,509 --> 00:47:29,597
Can we have a word?

773
00:47:30,492 --> 00:47:33,884
Sidney! What's going on?
Over here!

774
00:47:34,812 --> 00:47:36,093
Can you tell us anything?

775
00:47:36,221 --> 00:47:38,428
What's happening, Sidney?
What's going on?

776
00:47:38,556 --> 00:47:39,739
Sidney!

777
00:47:44,669 --> 00:47:47,228
The network texted.
They want us to go live.

778
00:47:47,356 --> 00:47:50,076
I'll go get Gale.
No! Don't.

779
00:47:50,204 --> 00:47:51,805
No. No, I'm not doing this.
Yes.

780
00:47:51,932 --> 00:47:53,820
They didn't specify
it had to be Gale.

781
00:47:53,948 --> 00:47:56,636
You'll get us fired!
Do it! Come on!

782
00:47:56,763 --> 00:47:58,716
Fine.

783
00:47:59,580 --> 00:48:02,779
Three, two, one-- Oh, boy.

784
00:48:04,157 --> 00:48:06,877
You try that again, and I'll
rip both your throats out.

785
00:48:07,005 --> 00:48:07,997
Got it?
Copy that.

786
00:48:08,125 --> 00:48:09,885
We just learned
that Gale Weathers

787
00:48:10,013 --> 00:48:13,052
from the now defunct talk show
<i>Good Morning with</i>
<i>Gale Weathers</i> is in town.

788
00:48:13,180 --> 00:48:14,299
Excuse me, Miss Weathers.

789
00:48:14,429 --> 00:48:16,413
Robbie Rivers, WFPO.
May I ask--

790
00:48:16,541 --> 00:48:18,365
Fuck the fuck off.
Okay.

791
00:48:18,492 --> 00:48:21,181
You two are a familiar sight.
What are you doing in town?

792
00:48:21,948 --> 00:48:23,037
Just passing through.

793
00:48:23,165 --> 00:48:24,445
With Gale Weathers?

794
00:48:24,572 --> 00:48:27,420
And you just happened
to run over
an escaped mental patient

795
00:48:27,548 --> 00:48:29,403
in front
of Sidney Evans's home?

796
00:48:29,532 --> 00:48:31,196
What's really
going on here?

797
00:48:31,323 --> 00:48:32,669
Why don't you
get your own story, Robbie.

798
00:48:32,797 --> 00:48:35,005
Yeah, we're not here
to do it for you.

799
00:48:35,901 --> 00:48:38,908
Come on, give a small-town
reporter his big break!

800
00:48:42,525 --> 00:48:44,892
Hey, Sidney.

801
00:48:45,019 --> 00:48:47,868
I'm so sorry this is happening
again, Mrs. Prescott.

802
00:48:48,796 --> 00:48:50,428
Mrs. Evans, Lucas.

803
00:48:50,556 --> 00:48:52,476
Right, yeah. Uh...

804
00:48:52,604 --> 00:48:53,885
Sorry, that's what I meant.

805
00:48:54,619 --> 00:48:56,252
Lucas, do you know
anything about A.I.?

806
00:48:56,380 --> 00:48:58,557
A.I.? Uh, I refuse.

807
00:48:58,685 --> 00:49:01,276
That is the death
of civilization.

808
00:49:01,405 --> 00:49:03,357
Why are you asking that?

809
00:49:04,092 --> 00:49:05,405
Just be careful, Jess.

810
00:49:05,532 --> 00:49:06,940
Keep your doors locked.

811
00:49:08,509 --> 00:49:10,716
Okay, come on, let's go.

812
00:49:13,628 --> 00:49:14,716
Oh, you're Gale Weathers. Hey.

813
00:49:14,845 --> 00:49:17,052
And who are you?
Uh...

814
00:49:17,468 --> 00:49:18,653
I'm Lucas.

815
00:49:19,228 --> 00:49:20,316
What are you doing here?

816
00:49:20,444 --> 00:49:22,589
He's my son,
and we live next door.

817
00:49:22,717 --> 00:49:24,379
We're friends
of the family.
Hmm.

818
00:49:24,509 --> 00:49:25,501
Yeah.

819
00:49:26,108 --> 00:49:27,741
You like horror movies, Lucas?

820
00:49:27,868 --> 00:49:29,693
Yeah, I lo-- I love them.

821
00:49:29,820 --> 00:49:31,452
Especially the <i>Stab</i> movies?

822
00:49:31,581 --> 00:49:32,796
Yeah,
I know them inside and out.

823
00:49:32,924 --> 00:49:34,812
What are you doing?
Mom, it's Gale Weathers.

824
00:49:34,939 --> 00:49:38,045
The <i>Stab</i> movies were based
on her true crime bestseller,
<i>The Woodsboro Murders.</i>

825
00:49:38,172 --> 00:49:40,700
I know, but I don't like
the way she's looking at you.

826
00:49:40,829 --> 00:49:44,220
Please leave my son out of
whatever it is you're doing.

827
00:49:45,180 --> 00:49:46,172
Sorry, kid,

828
00:49:46,300 --> 00:49:47,805
but you know how this works.

829
00:49:47,933 --> 00:49:48,829
Yeah.

830
00:49:48,956 --> 00:49:51,100
Everyone's a suspect.

831
00:49:51,228 --> 00:49:54,557
Well, yeah, but you killed
the killer. He's dead.

832
00:49:54,685 --> 00:49:55,868
Hmm.

833
00:49:56,892 --> 00:49:58,908
How do you know
there's just one?

834
00:50:00,349 --> 00:50:01,245
Excuse me.

835
00:50:01,373 --> 00:50:03,325
Whoa.

836
00:50:03,452 --> 00:50:07,260
Until this is over, I want you
to stay away from this house.

837
00:50:07,901 --> 00:50:09,212
Come on, let's go.

838
00:50:14,108 --> 00:50:15,805
How did you know to come?

839
00:50:15,932 --> 00:50:18,685
When the news broke
about the two murders
at the Macher house,

840
00:50:18,812 --> 00:50:22,045
a flock of reporters
raced to get there, but...

841
00:50:22,173 --> 00:50:24,540
my Sidney-sense told me
that Woodsboro was played out.

842
00:50:24,668 --> 00:50:28,604
Mark is having
the recorded calls analyzed
to confirm they're fake.

843
00:50:28,733 --> 00:50:30,749
Is it possible
they're real?

844
00:50:30,877 --> 00:50:32,252
Could Stu be alive?

845
00:50:32,380 --> 00:50:36,349
That would be
the better story,
but it's... too far-fetched.

846
00:50:36,477 --> 00:50:37,469
Hmm.

847
00:50:40,605 --> 00:50:41,788
What's going on?

848
00:50:41,916 --> 00:50:44,445
Oh, I just have
some nerve damage from the...

849
00:50:44,573 --> 00:50:46,493
from the attack in New York.

850
00:50:46,620 --> 00:50:47,708
You're lucky you sat
that one out.

851
00:50:47,837 --> 00:50:49,692
It-It was brutal.

852
00:50:50,333 --> 00:50:51,293
Thank you.

853
00:50:51,420 --> 00:50:52,669
It's nice to meet you, Tatum.

854
00:50:52,797 --> 00:50:54,524
Mmm. Tatum?

855
00:50:55,356 --> 00:50:57,021
Tatum as in...
That Tatum.

856
00:50:57,148 --> 00:50:58,268
Yeah.

857
00:50:58,397 --> 00:50:59,677
What do you two do for Gale?

858
00:50:59,805 --> 00:51:01,020
We're her hot interns.

859
00:51:01,148 --> 00:51:02,621
Ever since she got axed,

860
00:51:02,749 --> 00:51:04,349
she's been trying to
go back to her roots.

861
00:51:04,477 --> 00:51:07,261
So she's rebranding herself
as a crime reporter.

862
00:51:07,389 --> 00:51:08,860
She's teaching us
all she knows about the biz.

863
00:51:08,989 --> 00:51:10,748
Don't say "biz."
Yep.

864
00:51:10,877 --> 00:51:13,628
It's more like we're showing
Gale the ropes
of making premium content.

865
00:51:13,757 --> 00:51:15,037
Don't say "content."

866
00:51:15,165 --> 00:51:16,476
It's going great.

867
00:51:16,605 --> 00:51:17,660
Except Mindy keeps trying to
steal Gale's thunder.

868
00:51:17,789 --> 00:51:19,805
I'm the face of the future.
Sure.

869
00:51:19,932 --> 00:51:22,653
But in the meantime,
we're learning all about
fading careers

870
00:51:22,781 --> 00:51:24,317
and failed comebacks.

871
00:51:26,012 --> 00:51:27,421
Where are we gonna start?

872
00:51:28,220 --> 00:51:30,940
S-Start what? I'm...

873
00:51:32,189 --> 00:51:33,501
I'm not starting anything.

874
00:51:33,628 --> 00:51:35,900
We have to find out
who's behind this.

875
00:51:36,029 --> 00:51:37,468
That guy in the road,
Karl Gibbs,

876
00:51:37,596 --> 00:51:38,909
is not some random killer.

877
00:51:39,037 --> 00:51:41,500
It's always someone
connected to your past.

878
00:51:41,629 --> 00:51:42,941
The police can handle it.

879
00:51:43,069 --> 00:51:44,316
That would be
your husband.

880
00:51:44,445 --> 00:51:45,789
And we need to help him.

881
00:51:46,557 --> 00:51:48,253
Don't you want to
know who's behind this?

882
00:51:48,380 --> 00:51:50,589
Gale, I can't anymore.

883
00:51:50,717 --> 00:51:53,883
I need to be with my family,
I need to know they're safe.

884
00:51:54,013 --> 00:51:55,165
That's why
you need to help me.

885
00:51:55,293 --> 00:51:57,565
Whoever is targeting you
is not gonna stop...

886
00:51:57,692 --> 00:51:59,261
...you know that.

887
00:52:03,229 --> 00:52:06,909
<i>Oh, slap my face, if it</i>
<i>isn't the Gale Weathers!</i>

888
00:52:07,037 --> 00:52:08,188
<i>Hi. Oh, my God,</i>

889
00:52:08,316 --> 00:52:10,268
<i>I am so sorry</i>
<i>your show got canceled</i>

890
00:52:10,397 --> 00:52:12,060
<i>and then you got fired.</i>

891
00:52:12,188 --> 00:52:14,461
I wasn't fired.
My contract wasn't renewed.

892
00:52:14,589 --> 00:52:17,021
<i>So don't care.</i>
<i>Not even a little.</i>

893
00:52:17,149 --> 00:52:19,868
Ugh. I'm so sorry for
running over your friend.

894
00:52:19,997 --> 00:52:21,821
Can't do your own
dirty work, Stu?

895
00:52:23,485 --> 00:52:24,733
<i>Neither can you.</i>

896
00:52:24,860 --> 00:52:27,965
<i>You brought in some old,</i>
<i>irrelevant hag for backup.</i>

897
00:52:28,092 --> 00:52:29,245
<i>It's so sad.</i>

898
00:52:29,372 --> 00:52:30,589
<i>And what happened to</i>
<i>the two of you?</i>

899
00:52:30,717 --> 00:52:32,348
<i>You both had so much spunk.</i>

900
00:52:32,477 --> 00:52:34,717
You're gonna die,
you A.I. asshole.

901
00:52:34,845 --> 00:52:36,445
<i>We're going to see</i>
<i>how fake I am</i>

902
00:52:36,573 --> 00:52:38,525
<i>when I stab you</i>
<i>in the fucking throat!</i>

903
00:52:38,652 --> 00:52:39,996
<i>Because I'm coming for you</i>

904
00:52:40,125 --> 00:52:43,421
<i>and I'm gonna love</i>
<i>every second of it.</i>

905
00:52:48,252 --> 00:52:49,981
That was fucking weird.

906
00:52:52,733 --> 00:52:54,461
Fallbrook
Psychiatric Hospital.

907
00:52:54,589 --> 00:52:56,765
It's a couple hours away.
We'll start there.

908
00:52:58,236 --> 00:52:59,420
There she is.

909
00:53:00,189 --> 00:53:01,885
I knew you were
in there somewhere.

910
00:53:02,012 --> 00:53:05,405
You're right. This isn't
gonna stop unless I stop it.

911
00:53:12,413 --> 00:53:14,077
I'll be back as soon as I can.

912
00:53:14,205 --> 00:53:16,061
Mom, I want to go with you.

913
00:53:16,189 --> 00:53:17,981
No, sweetie, it's not safe.

914
00:53:18,109 --> 00:53:19,037
So why are you going?

915
00:53:19,165 --> 00:53:20,061
Because I know what I'm doing.

916
00:53:20,188 --> 00:53:21,341
Mom, please.

917
00:53:21,469 --> 00:53:22,717
You don't have
the skill set for this.

918
00:53:22,845 --> 00:53:24,413
Well, then show me.

919
00:53:25,213 --> 00:53:27,357
I don't want to end up like
the other Tatum.

920
00:53:28,605 --> 00:53:29,788
What?

921
00:53:30,589 --> 00:53:31,645
You named me after a girl who

922
00:53:31,772 --> 00:53:34,077
got her head crushed
in a garage door.

923
00:53:34,205 --> 00:53:36,252
She was my friend.
And she's dead!

924
00:53:37,885 --> 00:53:39,581
She was a-a victim,
not a fighter.

925
00:53:39,709 --> 00:53:42,012
I want to be a fighter.

926
00:53:42,141 --> 00:53:43,613
Honey. Listen--

927
00:53:43,741 --> 00:53:45,437
Nice to know what
you think of me.

928
00:53:54,109 --> 00:53:57,277
She just lost a friend,
so... she's upset.

929
00:53:58,237 --> 00:53:59,869
I want you to keep
her away from Ben.

930
00:53:59,997 --> 00:54:02,013
He's not to come over here.

931
00:54:02,141 --> 00:54:04,925
Someone was hiding
in the attic.
It could have been him.

932
00:54:05,052 --> 00:54:09,341
We are running traces on
all her friends' cell numbers,
emails and IP's.

933
00:54:09,469 --> 00:54:12,637
If Ben or any of her friends
are connected in any way

934
00:54:12,765 --> 00:54:13,948
we're gonna find it.

935
00:54:17,053 --> 00:54:20,477
She's right, you know.
Me protecting her from this,

936
00:54:21,117 --> 00:54:22,845
I made her vulnerable to it.

937
00:54:44,157 --> 00:54:45,149
Right.

938
00:54:46,365 --> 00:54:47,548
Okay.

939
00:54:48,349 --> 00:54:50,941
Okay, Terry. Thanks again.

940
00:54:53,021 --> 00:54:56,029
Woodsboro coroner says
there's no intake form
on Stu Macher's body.

941
00:54:56,156 --> 00:54:59,357
The woman who was coroner
in '96 died three years ago,

942
00:54:59,485 --> 00:55:00,509
so there's no one to ask.

943
00:55:00,637 --> 00:55:03,453
So it's a case
of lost paperwork?

944
00:55:03,581 --> 00:55:04,861
Or stolen paperwork.

945
00:55:04,989 --> 00:55:06,557
Someone who wants to
make it look like Stu's body

946
00:55:06,685 --> 00:55:08,157
never made it to the morgue.

947
00:55:09,341 --> 00:55:10,237
Or...

948
00:55:10,365 --> 00:55:11,581
It's actually Stu.

949
00:55:11,709 --> 00:55:13,564
Let's find out.
Yep.

950
00:55:14,396 --> 00:55:15,677
Here's your pass.
Thank you.

951
00:55:16,221 --> 00:55:17,117
Here you go.

952
00:55:17,245 --> 00:55:18,429
Thanks.

953
00:55:19,357 --> 00:55:20,797
How can I help you?

954
00:55:20,925 --> 00:55:22,076
Hi, I'm Gale Weathers.

955
00:55:22,204 --> 00:55:23,869
I'm a reporter
for Channel 7 in New York.

956
00:55:23,996 --> 00:55:25,277
Mm-hmm.

957
00:55:25,405 --> 00:55:26,973
We're doing a story
on Karl Gibbs.
I figured.

958
00:55:27,101 --> 00:55:30,525
The state police,
they were here all night
going through his stuff.

959
00:55:31,037 --> 00:55:32,221
Can we see his room?

960
00:55:32,764 --> 00:55:33,949
Well...

961
00:55:37,277 --> 00:55:39,837
Yeah, I guess so. Come on,
it's right down this way.

962
00:55:40,893 --> 00:55:42,909
So what can you
tell us about Karl?

963
00:55:43,037 --> 00:55:44,637
He was
a pretty violent guy.

964
00:55:45,661 --> 00:55:48,669
Killed three women
about 20 years ago.

965
00:55:51,325 --> 00:55:52,957
Can you think of any reason
that he would

966
00:55:53,085 --> 00:55:55,165
go after Sidney Prescott
and her family?

967
00:55:56,157 --> 00:55:58,077
No, not that I know of.

968
00:55:59,197 --> 00:56:00,797
I'm glad you're okay, though.

969
00:56:01,277 --> 00:56:02,813
Thanks.

970
00:56:05,853 --> 00:56:08,701
Did you ever hear him talk
about the Ghostface killings?

971
00:56:08,829 --> 00:56:11,613
Or the <i>Stab</i> movies,
or anything like that?

972
00:56:11,741 --> 00:56:12,797
Not that I remember.

973
00:56:12,925 --> 00:56:14,269
What about, um...

974
00:56:14,877 --> 00:56:15,773
him?

975
00:56:15,901 --> 00:56:18,013
Yeah, that's John.

976
00:56:18,844 --> 00:56:19,933
John?

977
00:56:20,060 --> 00:56:21,372
Yeah, as in John Doe.

978
00:56:21,501 --> 00:56:23,069
He didn't know his real name.

979
00:56:23,197 --> 00:56:24,669
He had amnesia from
the blow to the head

980
00:56:24,797 --> 00:56:26,557
that gave him all those scars.

981
00:56:26,685 --> 00:56:28,125
When did he arrive here?

982
00:56:28,253 --> 00:56:29,565
Well, it was before my time.

983
00:56:29,693 --> 00:56:33,981
I've been here 16 years.
So late '90s, maybe?

984
00:56:34,877 --> 00:56:37,277
His room was right down there.
You want to see it?

985
00:56:37,405 --> 00:56:38,621
Yes.

986
00:56:38,749 --> 00:56:40,509
You know, h-he was a drifter.

987
00:56:40,637 --> 00:56:43,677
Sleeping on the streets
of California or somewhere.

988
00:56:44,668 --> 00:56:46,877
And then one day he snapped.

989
00:56:47,517 --> 00:56:49,661
Attacked a high school girl.

990
00:56:49,789 --> 00:56:53,757
He was declared incompetent to
stand trial and ended up here.

991
00:56:54,589 --> 00:56:57,181
And where is he now?
He was released.

992
00:56:58,749 --> 00:57:00,477
Two weeks ago.

993
00:57:00,605 --> 00:57:03,004
Any idea where he went
after he was released?

994
00:57:03,901 --> 00:57:04,797
No, I'm sorry.

995
00:57:04,924 --> 00:57:05,949
But for that information

996
00:57:06,077 --> 00:57:07,997
you're gonna need
a court order.

997
00:57:08,125 --> 00:57:10,461
And I assume that John Doe
and Karl Gibbs

998
00:57:10,588 --> 00:57:11,900
spent a lot of time together?

999
00:57:12,029 --> 00:57:14,237
Oh, yeah.
No, they were good friends.

1000
00:57:14,366 --> 00:57:15,388
Yeah.

1001
00:57:15,517 --> 00:57:16,861
Very close.

1002
00:57:19,069 --> 00:57:20,253
Hmm.

1003
00:57:31,581 --> 00:57:32,764
Hmm.

1004
00:57:35,454 --> 00:57:36,573
Neighbor boy's sus.

1005
00:57:36,701 --> 00:57:38,845
He's out there
staring at the house.

1006
00:57:38,973 --> 00:57:40,222
Not subtle at all.

1007
00:57:40,797 --> 00:57:43,134
I've gone back three days.

1008
00:57:43,261 --> 00:57:44,540
If the killer was hiding
in the attic,

1009
00:57:44,669 --> 00:57:46,301
he had to go into
the house at some point.

1010
00:57:46,429 --> 00:57:48,445
Could the footage be hacked?

1011
00:57:48,573 --> 00:57:50,429
Clearly the killer
is tech savvy.

1012
00:57:50,557 --> 00:57:51,709
I don't know.

1013
00:57:51,837 --> 00:57:53,884
Uh, did you two find
the towels?

1014
00:57:54,013 --> 00:57:54,973
You got everything you need?

1015
00:57:55,100 --> 00:57:56,861
Yeah, the water
pressure was...

1016
00:57:56,989 --> 00:57:58,781
top-notch, so, thank you.

1017
00:57:58,909 --> 00:58:00,508
Yeah. Yeah, of course.

1018
00:58:01,277 --> 00:58:02,685
So, um...

1019
00:58:03,484 --> 00:58:04,700
Why are you here?

1020
00:58:05,725 --> 00:58:08,540
I'm sorry, I mean,
um...

1021
00:58:09,852 --> 00:58:11,517
After everything
you've been through,

1022
00:58:12,221 --> 00:58:13,117
aren't you scared?

1023
00:58:13,245 --> 00:58:15,645
Scared. Necessity.

1024
00:58:15,774 --> 00:58:18,909
My career trajectory
is to succeed
and exceed Gale Weathers.

1025
00:58:19,037 --> 00:58:21,980
And as Woodsboro legacy,
it is our duty.

1026
00:58:23,037 --> 00:58:25,245
Our uncle Randy was really
good friends with your mom.

1027
00:58:25,374 --> 00:58:28,125
And I want to uncover
the killer this time.

1028
00:58:28,254 --> 00:58:29,404
She has been wrong a lot.

1029
00:58:29,533 --> 00:58:30,749
That is not supportive.

1030
00:58:30,877 --> 00:58:33,982
Un-Uncover a killer?
How do you uncover a killer?

1031
00:58:34,108 --> 00:58:38,237
Assemble the suspects
and then Agatha Christie them
until they break.

1032
00:58:38,365 --> 00:58:39,933
So-- How do you
know who they are?

1033
00:58:40,061 --> 00:58:42,717
If history is any indication,
it's likely
one of your friends.

1034
00:58:42,844 --> 00:58:43,933
Probably your boyfriend.

1035
00:58:44,060 --> 00:58:45,597
Boyfriend's too obvious.

1036
00:58:45,724 --> 00:58:47,197
Unless it's by design.

1037
00:58:47,325 --> 00:58:48,285
It's not my boyfriend.

1038
00:58:48,414 --> 00:58:49,757
That's cute.

1039
00:58:49,885 --> 00:58:51,581
We need to gather all the
suspects together in one room.

1040
00:58:51,709 --> 00:58:55,453
Well, there's
a curfew at sundown.
The whole town's closing up.

1041
00:58:57,469 --> 00:58:58,845
Actually, there might be a way.

1042
00:58:58,974 --> 00:59:01,661
I just would have to figure
out how to get around my dad.

1043
00:59:01,790 --> 00:59:03,517
Is that possible?

1044
00:59:03,645 --> 00:59:05,245
He is the police chief.

1045
00:59:05,373 --> 00:59:08,253
But if we can find out
who's doing this,
then he can go get them.

1046
00:59:08,381 --> 00:59:10,045
If we can help, we should.

1047
00:59:12,029 --> 00:59:13,468
I'm sick of being useless.

1048
00:59:15,677 --> 00:59:17,086
That was Deputy Cooke.

1049
00:59:17,214 --> 00:59:19,613
They're set up to trace his
phone if he calls me again.

1050
00:59:19,741 --> 00:59:21,597
So we just have to
wait for him to call?

1051
00:59:21,725 --> 00:59:24,541
Oh, come on,
there's got to be some way to
bait him into calling you.

1052
00:59:25,886 --> 00:59:29,437
What if I gave you what you've
been asking me for since 1996?

1053
00:59:30,686 --> 00:59:31,869
An interview.

1054
00:59:33,980 --> 00:59:35,869
Get the fuck out of here.

1055
00:59:35,997 --> 00:59:37,885
Look, I just need an ETA
on that court order.

1056
00:59:38,013 --> 00:59:39,933
<i>You got it, Chief.</i>
<i>I'll take care of it.</i>

1057
00:59:40,061 --> 00:59:42,717
Good. Okay. Call me
the second Sid's phone rings.

1058
00:59:44,253 --> 00:59:45,148
Tatum!

1059
01:02:07,580 --> 01:02:09,982
Okay.
Get home safe. Bye, guys.

1060
01:02:36,894 --> 01:02:37,948
Hey.
Hey, Chlo.

1061
01:02:38,077 --> 01:02:39,293
Ben and Lucas
are already here.

1062
01:02:39,421 --> 01:02:42,430
All right. Uh,
this is Chad and Mindy.

1063
01:02:42,558 --> 01:02:44,350
Hi. I'm Chloe. Come on in.

1064
01:02:46,174 --> 01:02:48,061
So your parents
own this place.

1065
01:02:48,190 --> 01:02:50,749
Yes, but they
don't know we're here,
so we got to lay low.

1066
01:02:51,549 --> 01:02:52,733
How you doing?

1067
01:02:53,597 --> 01:02:55,389
What are
we drinking, kids?

1068
01:02:56,317 --> 01:02:57,533
Here is...

1069
01:02:57,662 --> 01:02:59,902
...the
pepperoni and mushroom pizza.

1070
01:03:00,028 --> 01:03:01,373
- Thanks, Chlo.
- Thank you.

1071
01:03:01,502 --> 01:03:03,165
So what is the deal
with you two?

1072
01:03:03,293 --> 01:03:06,013
Um, they want to help
us find out who's doing this.

1073
01:03:06,140 --> 01:03:09,020
What, they think
it's one of us?

1074
01:03:12,190 --> 01:03:14,493
Yeah. But I don't.

1075
01:03:15,709 --> 01:03:17,533
So this dead dude from thirty
years ago, he is not so dead?

1076
01:03:17,660 --> 01:03:19,580
How could Stu Macher
really be alive?

1077
01:03:20,157 --> 01:03:21,597
Where's he been? Under a rock?

1078
01:03:21,726 --> 01:03:23,549
Nobody recognized him
for three decades?

1079
01:03:23,677 --> 01:03:26,365
That's a ridiculous retcon
for any franchise.

1080
01:03:26,494 --> 01:03:29,245
See, this time it is
all about nostalgia.

1081
01:03:29,374 --> 01:03:31,453
Hey, Min! We talked about
the rules thing,

1082
01:03:31,582 --> 01:03:33,438
we said we weren't gonna
do that anymore. We're better
than that. So just...

1083
01:03:33,566 --> 01:03:37,246
Okay. Whoever it is
wants to bring Sidney
out of retirement.

1084
01:03:37,374 --> 01:03:40,190
She's a scream queen.
Scream queens are not allowed
to have happy endings.

1085
01:03:40,317 --> 01:03:43,933
There's a reason they
keep putting Jamie Lee
in new <i>Halloween</i> movies.

1086
01:03:44,062 --> 01:03:46,014
We all want to read
<i>Wuthering Heights</i>
again for the first time.

1087
01:03:46,141 --> 01:03:47,550
But this is real life.

1088
01:03:47,677 --> 01:03:49,340
Yes, exactly.

1089
01:03:49,470 --> 01:03:51,774
This person isn't a fan of
<i>Stab</i> movies,

1090
01:03:51,901 --> 01:03:54,205
they're a fan of
Sidney Prescott.

1091
01:03:54,334 --> 01:03:55,965
Not the Sidney of today,
though.

1092
01:03:56,093 --> 01:03:58,398
The Sidney
of thirty years ago.

1093
01:03:58,526 --> 01:04:01,342
The Sidney that was killing
Ghostfaces, like, once a year.

1094
01:04:01,468 --> 01:04:03,773
And the reason they're using
Stu Macher to fuck with her

1095
01:04:03,902 --> 01:04:06,364
is because he was
there at the start.

1096
01:04:06,493 --> 01:04:10,108
The night Sidney the
Avenging Angel was born.

1097
01:04:11,934 --> 01:04:14,109
Or it really is Stu.
I mean, Billy Loomis
had a secret love child,

1098
01:04:14,237 --> 01:04:15,964
so who the fuck knows anymore?

1099
01:04:16,093 --> 01:04:17,533
Where'd you get these calls?
Uh...

1100
01:04:17,662 --> 01:04:20,957
My mom's cloud. Can you
tell if they're fake or not?

1101
01:04:21,085 --> 01:04:22,366
If it's a fake,
it's a good one.
Hmm.

1102
01:04:22,494 --> 01:04:24,126
The shadows are consistent.

1103
01:04:24,253 --> 01:04:27,517
The eyes, hands, they all have
zero artifacts or pixilation.
I mean...

1104
01:04:27,645 --> 01:04:28,862
These might have
been live calls.

1105
01:04:28,990 --> 01:04:31,710
All right, well,
if it is Stu Macher

1106
01:04:31,837 --> 01:04:33,822
then we know
he has an accomplice.

1107
01:04:33,950 --> 01:04:36,446
He can't be in two
places at once, so...

1108
01:04:37,886 --> 01:04:39,229
who is it?

1109
01:04:39,358 --> 01:04:41,117
Why would any of us want to
terrorize Tatum and her mom?

1110
01:04:41,246 --> 01:04:44,510
Why indeed. Let's talk motive.

1111
01:04:44,637 --> 01:04:46,078
Pardon. Thank you.

1112
01:04:46,206 --> 01:04:48,350
Okay, Ben.
Mmm.

1113
01:04:48,477 --> 01:04:51,006
Does Sidney truly approve
of you as Tatum's boyfriend?

1114
01:04:51,133 --> 01:04:54,620
Moms never like the boyfriend.
That's Mommy 101, there.

1115
01:04:54,750 --> 01:04:57,630
And you're an interesting
mix of brawn and brains.

1116
01:04:57,757 --> 01:05:00,189
Nah. I like to work out
my body and my mind, yeah.

1117
01:05:00,317 --> 01:05:02,013
See, that's incredibly
bizarre to say out loud.

1118
01:05:02,141 --> 01:05:03,774
Chloe.

1119
01:05:03,901 --> 01:05:05,630
- Hey.
- Fun-loving. Everyone likes.

1120
01:05:05,757 --> 01:05:08,126
Excellent hair.
Seemingly has no motive.

1121
01:05:08,254 --> 01:05:09,438
That's me.

1122
01:05:09,566 --> 01:05:10,717
- I'm not buying it.
- Good.

1123
01:05:10,845 --> 01:05:12,318
I don't like a girl
that everyone likes.

1124
01:05:12,446 --> 01:05:13,725
It's boring.

1125
01:05:13,854 --> 01:05:16,030
Oh. See? That's motive.

1126
01:05:16,158 --> 01:05:18,782
Right? Boredom? Now we're
in Stu Macher territory.

1127
01:05:18,910 --> 01:05:20,830
And you, weird boy.
Okay.

1128
01:05:20,958 --> 01:05:24,446
You've displayed
an unsettling obsession with
all things Sidney Prescott.

1129
01:05:24,574 --> 01:05:26,366
She's a pinnacle in
the true-crime lexicon.

1130
01:05:26,494 --> 01:05:27,964
I'm not obsessed.
I'm just...

1131
01:05:28,093 --> 01:05:30,909
I'm, uh, fascinated.

1132
01:05:31,037 --> 01:05:33,470
Splitting hairs,
young man.

1133
01:05:33,597 --> 01:05:34,845
Okay, my money's on boyfriend.

1134
01:05:34,974 --> 01:05:36,318
Yeah, my bet's
on creepy kid.

1135
01:05:36,446 --> 01:05:37,661
Okay,
I'm pretty fucking sick of

1136
01:05:37,789 --> 01:05:39,357
all this "creepy" shit,
all right?

1137
01:05:39,484 --> 01:05:40,894
I'm not creepy.

1138
01:05:41,022 --> 01:05:43,070
Creepy is kind of hot.

1139
01:05:45,213 --> 01:05:46,750
Oh.
Hey.

1140
01:05:46,878 --> 01:05:48,061
Hey.

1141
01:05:49,149 --> 01:05:50,590
Can I have another beer?

1142
01:05:50,718 --> 01:05:52,157
You can have
whatever you want.

1143
01:05:55,614 --> 01:05:58,206
And per our discussion,
this is my exclusive.

1144
01:05:58,333 --> 01:06:00,126
- That was the deal.
- Yeah, yeah. Got it.

1145
01:06:00,253 --> 01:06:02,366
- Okay.
- There you go.

1146
01:06:02,493 --> 01:06:03,709
Oh, okay.

1147
01:06:03,838 --> 01:06:05,373
Oh. There.

1148
01:06:06,686 --> 01:06:08,317
All right,
I have three cameras on you.

1149
01:06:08,445 --> 01:06:10,108
We'll be operating from
the control room.

1150
01:06:10,237 --> 01:06:12,894
We need your phone,
so when he calls...

1151
01:06:13,502 --> 01:06:15,613
Thank you.
All right, ladies,

1152
01:06:15,742 --> 01:06:19,326
we'll be ready to break into
every affiliate in the state
on your go.

1153
01:06:19,965 --> 01:06:22,078
Jesus, this is
fucking awesome!

1154
01:06:22,684 --> 01:06:23,773
Okay.

1155
01:06:23,901 --> 01:06:25,950
Let's just hope that
Stu is watching.

1156
01:06:26,428 --> 01:06:27,421
Ready?

1157
01:06:27,549 --> 01:06:29,565
You gonna play nice?
Of course not.

1158
01:06:29,694 --> 01:06:32,734
I've been waiting for this
interview for thirty years.

1159
01:06:32,862 --> 01:06:34,301
And three, two...

1160
01:06:36,350 --> 01:06:40,734
Hi, I'm Gale Weathers
here for an exclusive interview
with Sidney Prescott.

1161
01:06:44,733 --> 01:06:46,046
What the hell?

1162
01:06:46,174 --> 01:06:49,022
My mom's going live on TV.
Channel 7.

1163
01:06:49,150 --> 01:06:50,142
Oh.

1164
01:06:52,830 --> 01:06:55,134
<i>Welcome, Sidney. Hi.</i>
<i>Hi, Gale.</i>

1165
01:06:55,261 --> 01:06:59,325
<i>So everyone knows you as</i>
<i>the survivor of</i>
<i>many brutal attacks.</i>

1166
01:06:59,454 --> 01:07:03,678
<i>And I understand that</i>
<i>you and your family</i>
<i>are once again a target.</i>

1167
01:07:03,806 --> 01:07:05,726
Can you explain
what's happening?

1168
01:07:05,853 --> 01:07:07,773
My family and I
have been attacked twice now

1169
01:07:07,901 --> 01:07:10,430
by someone claiming to be
Stu Macher.

1170
01:07:10,557 --> 01:07:12,573
But Stu was
killed in Woodsboro

1171
01:07:12,701 --> 01:07:15,613
the night that he
and Billy Loomis attacked you.

1172
01:07:15,741 --> 01:07:19,261
Yes, but now
I'm not so sure.

1173
01:07:19,389 --> 01:07:21,309
Is that why you're doing
this interview?

1174
01:07:21,438 --> 01:07:24,124
I want to talk to him.
What would you
like to say?

1175
01:07:24,253 --> 01:07:26,686
I want to know
what he wants.

1176
01:07:26,814 --> 01:07:29,470
Why he's doing this
after all of these years.

1177
01:07:29,598 --> 01:07:31,198
I want him to know that

1178
01:07:32,094 --> 01:07:33,693
this doesn't need to continue.

1179
01:07:33,821 --> 01:07:35,454
Zoom in.
Tighter, tighter.

1180
01:07:35,581 --> 01:07:37,854
Whatever you need, let's talk.

1181
01:07:37,982 --> 01:07:38,974
Hmm.

1182
01:07:40,093 --> 01:07:42,206
Maybe he's too much of
a little bitch.

1183
01:07:43,006 --> 01:07:45,757
He always was the sidekick,
never the lead.

1184
01:07:47,870 --> 01:07:49,310
Is that what it is?

1185
01:07:49,438 --> 01:07:52,638
You want to be the lead?
Well, here you go.

1186
01:07:52,766 --> 01:07:54,558
<i>Call me. You have a platform.</i>

1187
01:07:54,686 --> 01:07:55,998
Oh, shit.

1188
01:08:00,062 --> 01:08:03,484
Maybe he hasn't tuned in yet.
Let's keep talking.

1189
01:08:04,444 --> 01:08:06,718
You and I have known
each other a long time.

1190
01:08:07,454 --> 01:08:09,148
A very long time, yes.

1191
01:08:09,277 --> 01:08:11,197
How would you describe
our relationship?

1192
01:08:12,254 --> 01:08:14,141
Complicated but enduring.

1193
01:08:15,261 --> 01:08:17,118
You wrote a book,
<i>Out of Darkness,</i>

1194
01:08:17,246 --> 01:08:19,038
<i>about healing your trauma.</i>

1195
01:08:19,166 --> 01:08:21,597
<i>And yet you have</i>
<i>completely disappeared</i>

1196
01:08:21,724 --> 01:08:24,253
<i>from the public eye</i>
<i>for years now. Why?</i>

1197
01:08:24,382 --> 01:08:28,158
<i>It just seemed</i>
<i>the more I talked about it,</i>
<i>the more darkness came.</i>

1198
01:08:28,286 --> 01:08:29,246
Mmm.

1199
01:08:29,373 --> 01:08:30,526
You have three children.

1200
01:08:30,654 --> 01:08:33,022
Tatum being your oldest.
She's seventeen?

1201
01:08:33,148 --> 01:08:34,717
I'd rather not talk about
my children.

1202
01:08:34,846 --> 01:08:38,398
Tatum is the same age
that you were
when this whole thing started.

1203
01:08:38,526 --> 01:08:40,542
That must have
a huge significance for you.

1204
01:08:40,670 --> 01:08:42,877
Like I said, I don't want to
talk about my kids.

1205
01:08:43,006 --> 01:08:45,021
<i>And you named your kid Tatum</i>

1206
01:08:45,150 --> 01:08:48,766
<i>after the young girl who was</i>
<i>brutally murdered</i>
<i>all those years ago.</i>

1207
01:08:48,894 --> 01:08:52,606
I named her after a childhood
friend whom I loved dearly.

1208
01:08:54,301 --> 01:08:56,670
She was the last friend
I ever trusted.

1209
01:08:58,461 --> 01:08:59,454
Mmm.

1210
01:09:00,124 --> 01:09:01,214
Sidney, do you ever
worry about

1211
01:09:01,341 --> 01:09:03,486
passing your trauma on
to your children?

1212
01:09:03,613 --> 01:09:04,828
Or, even worse yet,

1213
01:09:04,957 --> 01:09:06,748
that they would be
the target of future killings?

1214
01:09:06,877 --> 01:09:08,030
Oh, shit.

1215
01:09:08,158 --> 01:09:10,078
Sidney?
Okay, Gale, stop.

1216
01:09:12,350 --> 01:09:14,846
Where's she going?
Okay, we'll be right back.

1217
01:09:14,974 --> 01:09:17,182
Or maybe not. Cut.

1218
01:09:17,308 --> 01:09:18,333
All right.

1219
01:09:18,462 --> 01:09:20,414
Um... Go to the outro
and stand by.

1220
01:09:20,541 --> 01:09:22,366
Wh--

1221
01:09:24,830 --> 01:09:26,078
That was unfair.

1222
01:09:26,494 --> 01:09:28,158
And dangerous!

1223
01:09:28,286 --> 01:09:30,654
But you disappeared, Sid.
People want to know.

1224
01:09:30,781 --> 01:09:32,286
I want to know!

1225
01:09:33,086 --> 01:09:35,038
I'm sorry.
Are you?

1226
01:09:35,166 --> 01:09:38,366
What if I had asked you
about Dewey on live TV?

1227
01:09:38,493 --> 01:09:39,388
What would you say?

1228
01:09:39,518 --> 01:09:41,790
Well, I'd say I'm fine.

1229
01:09:43,038 --> 01:09:46,108
Because that's what I
tell myself 500 times a day

1230
01:09:46,238 --> 01:09:48,254
just to get through the day.

1231
01:10:07,261 --> 01:10:10,046
<i>This has been a Robbie Rivers</i>
<i>exclusive with Gale Weathers</i>

1232
01:10:10,173 --> 01:10:12,926
<i>and Pine Grove's very</i>
<i>own Sidney Prescott Evans.</i>

1233
01:10:13,085 --> 01:10:14,462
<i>We will be monitoring--</i>

1234
01:10:14,590 --> 01:10:16,286
That was intense.

1235
01:10:17,726 --> 01:10:18,910
Yeah.

1236
01:10:19,550 --> 01:10:20,733
Are you okay?

1237
01:10:23,581 --> 01:10:25,117
I'm sorry this is happening.

1238
01:10:25,790 --> 01:10:28,190
And this--
This was a dumb idea.

1239
01:10:28,317 --> 01:10:29,534
How far is the TV station?

1240
01:10:29,661 --> 01:10:31,390
I just really want to be with
my mom right now.

1241
01:10:31,518 --> 01:10:33,278
We're super close.
I mean, I'll take you.

1242
01:10:33,757 --> 01:10:35,006
Okay.

1243
01:10:41,630 --> 01:10:42,748
We're not on air.

1244
01:10:42,878 --> 01:10:44,734
And this needs to be
on air.
Hello?

1245
01:10:44,862 --> 01:10:47,390
<i>Aw, Sid, do you need a hug?</i>

1246
01:10:49,022 --> 01:10:50,494
We've been waiting for you.

1247
01:10:50,622 --> 01:10:51,678
<i>Why? So I can</i>
<i>stay on the phone</i>

1248
01:10:51,806 --> 01:10:53,118
<i>long enough for you to</i>
<i>trace the call?</i>

1249
01:10:53,246 --> 01:10:55,902
Yes, dumbass! Or you could
just tell us where you are.

1250
01:10:56,030 --> 01:10:58,782
<i>Great. I am at Parker's Tavern</i>

1251
01:10:58,910 --> 01:11:00,574
<i>with your daughter.</i>

1252
01:11:01,310 --> 01:11:02,814
My daughter's not at Parker's.

1253
01:11:02,942 --> 01:11:04,477
<i>Well, she's definitely not</i>
