By killing you.

1533
01:35:05,504 --> 01:35:06,911
No more baggage.

1534
01:35:07,806 --> 01:35:09,630
I am releasing it all.

1535
01:35:10,559 --> 01:35:11,806
What about Lucas?
You have a son.

1536
01:35:11,935 --> 01:35:14,304
Oh, no, no. He's gone, Sid.

1537
01:35:14,430 --> 01:35:16,639
I mean, he was too much
like his father.

1538
01:35:17,088 --> 01:35:18,270
And now

1539
01:35:19,326 --> 01:35:21,215
I can have a new beginning.

1540
01:35:25,471 --> 01:35:27,839
Do you think that you've been
a good mother to Tatum?

1541
01:35:28,991 --> 01:35:31,935
I mean, you really haven't
taught her anything useful,
am I right?

1542
01:35:34,368 --> 01:35:36,671
You've kept the survivor
all to yourself.

1543
01:35:36,799 --> 01:35:39,936
But that's okay.
Because I'm gonna teach her!

1544
01:35:43,263 --> 01:35:45,792
She's gonna watch
her mother die.

1545
01:35:45,920 --> 01:35:47,583
Just like you did.

1546
01:35:48,895 --> 01:35:50,463
The cycle continues.

1547
01:35:50,592 --> 01:35:51,552
No.

1548
01:35:51,680 --> 01:35:53,472
You see,
it finally dawned on me.

1549
01:35:54,528 --> 01:35:56,256
I don't need you.

1550
01:35:56,384 --> 01:35:58,623
I mean, none of us do.
Let's face it,

1551
01:35:58,751 --> 01:36:01,599
you're kind of past your prime
for a final girl.

1552
01:36:02,144 --> 01:36:04,606
I'm creating Sidney 2.0.

1553
01:36:05,503 --> 01:36:07,326
Watch closely, Tatum.

1554
